HEADWORD: Water flannel
<hw>Wa"ter flan"nel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A floating
mass formed in pools by the entangled filaments of a European
fresh-water alga (<spn>Cladophora crispata</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

